@startuml
title Viaverse Dynamic Environment / Matching — Sequence Diagram

actor Client
participant "API Gateway / BFF" as BFF
participant "taxonomy-service" as Taxonomy
participant "profile/preferences" as Profile
participant "search-service" as Search
participant "trust-service" as Trust
participant "analytics/AI" as Analytics
queue "Outbox / Kafka" as Kafka

Client -> BFF : GET /feed or /matches
BFF -> Taxonomy : resolve categories/tags/forms
Taxonomy -> Profile : load dynamic environment\narea/interests
Taxonomy -> Search : build search filters\ncategory + geo + intent
Search -> Trust : trust/risk/availability signals
Search -> Analytics : ranking feedback / AI suggestion
Taxonomy -> Kafka : CategoryMapped / DynamicEnvUsed
Taxonomy --> BFF : filter schema + result hints
BFF --> Client : render feed/search

note bottom
Dynamic environment combines area, interests, category intent,
provider capability and trust signals.
It is not a fixed neighborhood/community boundary.
end note
@enduml
